reviews_data.review_text:
We have been fans of Common Market for a minute now. First the food, then the atmosphere, and now part of our Thanksgiving tradition. We ordered a smoked chicken, 1 lb of BBQ pork, Mac n Cheese and the Feta Vegetable Hash.

In a city where every place has a BBQ pork and thinks it’s the best, I can assure you, this one hold sit own. Smokey, peppery, rich and comforting, like good BBQ should be. For every dozen craft BBQ shops with artisan pickles and house made vinegar sauce, there’s a Common Market, making food with love.

I’m glad we found Common Market and I’m very glad we tried them for Thanksgiving. Go there and taste the love they put into all their food.

reviews_data.review_text: Very disappointed with the quality of the food lately. I came for the their famous homemade onion rings to get greasy frozen store bought onion rings. Their chicken sandwich is not what it used to be either.

Got a Reubon, which had little to no meat and mostly consisted of copious amounts of sauerkraut with no 1,000 Islands or any dressing of any kind. When we showed it to the deli counter, they refused to remake it or add more meat to my sandwich, or offer a solution to the problem. Horrible customer service.

I won't be back.

Thanks Chase!  We appreciate your narrative as to what happened as well as including pictures.  For reference the light colored pink sauce in your picture is 1,000 island dressing.

Matt, our employee in the deli, fielded your complaint at 1:35pm about your sandwich lacking enough meat and offered to heat up additional corned beef as an attempt address your dissatisfaction.  Matt politely did this and you returned to the pick up window two minutes later and added the additional corned beef to your sandwich at the table in front of the coffee.  You appeared to finish the entire thing and left the store.  

We are stumped that your review and narrative do not line up with what the cameras showed from our end so perhaps you could provide additional clarification about the interaction that we could use to improve our business.

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Good afternoon, Cameron,

Thank you for your feedback. When a guest brings a bad experience to light it means that 10 other people had the same experience and just didn’t say anything. We appreciate you sharing these thoughts with us and giving us a chance to improve what we do. 

Thank you also for being a returning guest. We obviously did something right in the past for you to come back. Which makes your comments disheartening for us. We work hard to provide good food, products, and service. Something you recognized in the past and brought you back. That fact alone compounds the gravity of our failure when you visited us last. 

We do understand that our system can be a little confusing for first-time visitors. Where to place your order; where to pick it up; which menu to order from and where to find them – all are questions new guests have when they first walk in. We have signage around the store but we also work with our staff to make sure all of this information is delivered verbally at the point of service to proactively allay their confusion.

Apparently, you came right during the transition between our lunch and dinner service. You were incorrectly directed to our lunch menu, then told you couldn’t order from that menu, then not given a night menu, not informed about wait time or pick-up about your food and then left at the bar without being offered a refill. 

All those missteps from our staff and you still left a good tip – and that speaks volumes about your character.

We wouldn’t be surprised if you never came back. To your point, there are many places for you to spend that kind of money and not have to flag someone over for another beer. 

We obviously have a huge gap in our training with some of our retail staff for inconsistencies like this to all happen in a single experience. We cannot and will not try to make excuses as this one is completely on us. Your review has given the entire team here a pause for reflection on what we can do to make sure this doesn’t happen to you or anyone else again. 

While we know that replies and apologies won’t make up for your poor experience that evening we would hate to lose you as a return guest. We sincerely hope you‘ll give us another chance. Suffice to say, your next meal there will be on us.

Whether or not you do come back we’d like to, once again, thank you for you past support and for your timely feedback on your recent visit.

I went to to the counter to make night time food order and neither of the employees acknowledged my presence! I know for a fact that this is a case of discrimination! reviews_data.owner_answer:
Good day, Ashanti,

Thank you for the feedback on your service at our Oakwold store. As you said, you have been there many times and we have been happy to serve you there every time you have been there. The largest part of success of any small business is the repeat customers they get and you have been one of them. We have always been excited and supportive of your farming efforts here in Charlotte, whether they have been with our other community partners or with your solo venture moving into 2022. It has never mattered to us whether you have been there to order food or just to charge your phone you have been a welcome presence.

While we take all feedback seriously, that from our return guests, such as yourself, carry a little more weight. As it should. Which is why this review is particularly disheartening.

We won’t argue that you may have received poor service that night. From a hospitality perspective, “Good Service” is something that requires constant training and accountability and is, apparently, an area in which we fell short this particular evening.

But we would like to state this. The very first brick in the foundation of what makes the Common Market the Common Market is that Everyone is Welcome.

Given your history of visiting the store I might offer that your experience was one born of lack of training rather than intentful discrimination. We spend a lot of time training and shaping our culture to be 100% inclusive regardless of color of skin, gender or gender identity, sexual orientation, political affiliation, socioeconomic status or religion. This is a core value upon which we build everything else in our business.

We are not spelling this out to diminish how you felt. More to validate it. Part of understanding inclusion is understanding implicit biases and how they can shape our everyday interactions. We are all susceptible to them – guests and service providers alike. As much as we include that in our training, experiences such as yours affirm the continued need for us to stress that with intention.

Ashanti, we appreciate your past patronage and support and genuinely hope we can earn it again in the future.

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Good morning, Rachael,

Thank you for your feedback. As always, we appreciate our guests bringing their concerns to us, especially when it gives us a chance to improve our service or our food. One philosophy we work hard to impart on our employees is that, “Good food can’t save poor service but great service can save a poorly prepared meal.” It is obvious from your review that at least one of our employees hasn’t taken that completely to heart.

A clarification on our night menu: To your point we haven’t been doing it for over a year. We started testing our night menus in April of last year and have been running them successfully ever since. We are coming up on our first full year of running the late night menu so his timing is a little off. It is true that we do not offer our regular sandwich menu Tuesdays through Saturdays from 5 pm until 9 pm. Those are the hours where we serve our night menu exclusively.  I am assuming you must visit us mostly for lunch or breakfast, so I can appreciate your disappointment when you were not able to order an item you probably had your heart set on. I hope, at the very least, you enjoyed what you ordered from our kitchen last night.

That being said, I can also appreciate the possibility that the service you received most likely left a bad taste in your mouth and detracted from the food no matter how well it was prepared. This is certainly something we will address internally. we have spoken to the employee who provided your service last night and he had nothing to amend your take on his service.

We, of course, apologize for the abrasive service you received and would love a chance to make it up to you. If you don’t, we understand. There are many places you can choose in Charlotte and we let you down when you chose us last night.

Thanks again for your feedback as we always look forward to the opportunity to become better at what we do!

reviews_data.review_text: Girlfriend asked for vegan chili, and was served chili with meat in it, she also got a vegan sandwich and asked for no cream cheese...guess what was on her sandwich. reviews_data.owner_answer:
Jackson - I first want to apologize for the delayed response.  We had issues with our Google account not letting us respond to reviews and it has finally been resolved.

Thank you for your feedback on your experience at our Monroe Rd store. We look to any feedback to constantly improve our guest service experience and we appreciate your candor.

I’d like to begin by assuring you that the chili we served you was indeed vegan. We 100% value the business of all our guests with special dietary needs and restriction which is why we go to great pains to keep so many vegan and gluten-free options on our menu and in our daily specials.

We only served three soups the day of your review– Vegan Chili, Vegan Tomato and our Kofta Soup (which is white).  Our prep manager has been working hard on making a delectable vegan chili. It’s a new recipe for us this year and differs from our vegan chili last year in that we have included a healthy amount of No Evil Foods chorizo as the flavor base for the recipe. If you are familiar with No Evil Foods you will know that their seitan-based protein analogs a very, very close to the real thing. In my years of using their product I have often been accused of serving vegans and vegetarians actual meat. So maybe our vegan chili is too close? It was something we considered when we first made this new soup and you have certainly given us more food for thought.

As for the cream cheese, we did find your ticket. I believe you had a Tree Hugger, a Reuben and the Chili. Please correct me if I’m wrong. The way our kitchen entered your ticket was a “Tree Hugger add Hummus” as opposed to a “Tree Hugger sub Hummus for Cream Cheese”. That is entirely on us. As I said, we place a high priority on our special diets production. We know how hard it can be for vegans and vegetarians to find quality meals in our area and strive to offer ourselves as a go-to option for those looking for a diverse selection. There are many places to eat in Charlotte and you chose us. If you’d care to give us another try, we’d love to buy a sandwich for you the next time you come in as one small way to make up for our error.

Good afternoon, Cameron,

Thank you for your feedback. When a guest brings a bad experience to light it means that 10 other people had the same experience and just didn’t say anything. We appreciate you sharing these thoughts with us and giving us a chance to improve what we do. 

Thank you also for being a returning guest. We obviously did something right in the past for you to come back. Which makes your comments disheartening for us. We work hard to provide good food, products, and service. Something you recognized in the past and brought you back. That fact alone compounds the gravity of our failure when you visited us last. 

We do understand that our system can be a little confusing for first-time visitors. Where to place your order; where to pick it up; which menu to order from and where to find them – all are questions new guests have when they first walk in. We have signage around the store but we also work with our staff to make sure all of this information is delivered verbally at the point of service to proactively allay their confusion.

Apparently, you came right during the transition between our lunch and dinner service. You were incorrectly directed to our lunch menu, then told you couldn’t order from that menu, then not given a night menu, not informed about wait time or pick-up about your food and then left at the bar without being offered a refill. 

All those missteps from our staff and you still left a good tip – and that speaks volumes about your character.

We wouldn’t be surprised if you never came back. To your point, there are many places for you to spend that kind of money and not have to flag someone over for another beer. 

We obviously have a huge gap in our training with some of our retail staff for inconsistencies like this to all happen in a single experience. We cannot and will not try to make excuses as this one is completely on us. Your review has given the entire team here a pause for reflection on what we can do to make sure this doesn’t happen to you or anyone else again. 

While we know that replies and apologies won’t make up for your poor experience that evening we would hate to lose you as a return guest. We sincerely hope you‘ll give us another chance. Suffice to say, your next meal there will be on us.

Whether or not you do come back we’d like to, once again, thank you for you past support and for your timely feedback on your recent visit.

I went to to the counter to make night time food order and neither of the employees acknowledged my presence! I know for a fact that this is a case of discrimination! reviews_data.owner_answer:
Good day, Ashanti,

Thank you for the feedback on your service at our Oakwold store. As you said, you have been there many times and we have been happy to serve you there every time you have been there. The largest part of success of any small business is the repeat customers they get and you have been one of them. We have always been excited and supportive of your farming efforts here in Charlotte, whether they have been with our other community partners or with your solo venture moving into 2022. It has never mattered to us whether you have been there to order food or just to charge your phone you have been a welcome presence.

While we take all feedback seriously, that from our return guests, such as yourself, carry a little more weight. As it should. Which is why this review is particularly disheartening.

We won’t argue that you may have received poor service that night. From a hospitality perspective, “Good Service” is something that requires constant training and accountability and is, apparently, an area in which we fell short this particular evening.

But we would like to state this. The very first brick in the foundation of what makes the Common Market the Common Market is that Everyone is Welcome.

Given your history of visiting the store I might offer that your experience was one born of lack of training rather than intentful discrimination. We spend a lot of time training and shaping our culture to be 100% inclusive regardless of color of skin, gender or gender identity, sexual orientation, political affiliation, socioeconomic status or religion. This is a core value upon which we build everything else in our business.

We are not spelling this out to diminish how you felt. More to validate it. Part of understanding inclusion is understanding implicit biases and how they can shape our everyday interactions. We are all susceptible to them – guests and service providers alike. As much as we include that in our training, experiences such as yours affirm the continued need for us to stress that with intention.

Ashanti, we appreciate your past patronage and support and genuinely hope we can earn it again in the future.

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Good morning, Rachael,

Thank you for your feedback. As always, we appreciate our guests bringing their concerns to us, especially when it gives us a chance to improve our service or our food. One philosophy we work hard to impart on our employees is that, “Good food can’t save poor service but great service can save a poorly prepared meal.” It is obvious from your review that at least one of our employees hasn’t taken that completely to heart.

A clarification on our night menu: To your point we haven’t been doing it for over a year. We started testing our night menus in April of last year and have been running them successfully ever since. We are coming up on our first full year of running the late night menu so his timing is a little off. It is true that we do not offer our regular sandwich menu Tuesdays through Saturdays from 5 pm until 9 pm. Those are the hours where we serve our night menu exclusively.  I am assuming you must visit us mostly for lunch or breakfast, so I can appreciate your disappointment when you were not able to order an item you probably had your heart set on. I hope, at the very least, you enjoyed what you ordered from our kitchen last night.

That being said, I can also appreciate the possibility that the service you received most likely left a bad taste in your mouth and detracted from the food no matter how well it was prepared. This is certainly something we will address internally. we have spoken to the employee who provided your service last night and he had nothing to amend your take on his service.

We, of course, apologize for the abrasive service you received and would love a chance to make it up to you. If you don’t, we understand. There are many places you can choose in Charlotte and we let you down when you chose us last night.

Thanks again for your feedback as we always look forward to the opportunity to become better at what we do!

Jackson - I first want to apologize for the delayed response.  We had issues with our Google account not letting us respond to reviews and it has finally been resolved.

Thank you for your feedback on your experience at our Monroe Rd store. We look to any feedback to constantly improve our guest service experience and we appreciate your candor.

I’d like to begin by assuring you that the chili we served you was indeed vegan. We 100% value the business of all our guests with special dietary needs and restriction which is why we go to great pains to keep so many vegan and gluten-free options on our menu and in our daily specials.

We only served three soups the day of your review– Vegan Chili, Vegan Tomato and our Kofta Soup (which is white).  Our prep manager has been working hard on making a delectable vegan chili. It’s a new recipe for us this year and differs from our vegan chili last year in that we have included a healthy amount of No Evil Foods chorizo as the flavor base for the recipe. If you are familiar with No Evil Foods you will know that their seitan-based protein analogs a very, very close to the real thing. In my years of using their product I have often been accused of serving vegans and vegetarians actual meat. So maybe our vegan chili is too close? It was something we considered when we first made this new soup and you have certainly given us more food for thought.

As for the cream cheese, we did find your ticket. I believe you had a Tree Hugger, a Reuben and the Chili. Please correct me if I’m wrong. The way our kitchen entered your ticket was a “Tree Hugger add Hummus” as opposed to a “Tree Hugger sub Hummus for Cream Cheese”. That is entirely on us. As I said, we place a high priority on our special diets production. We know how hard it can be for vegans and vegetarians to find quality meals in our area and strive to offer ourselves as a go-to option for those looking for a diverse selection. There are many places to eat in Charlotte and you chose us. If you’d care to give us another try, we’d love to buy a sandwich for you the next time you come in as one small way to make up for our error.

reviews_data.review_text: Great local neighborhood joint offering a varied selection of unique high quality beers, wines,  coffees, foods, snacks etc...Known for their creative breakfast and lunch sandwiches, eclectic feel and laid back atmosphere this location may soon offer prepared take away foods for dinner. As of early May 2017 they are still working on stocking the store since they JUST opened and I look forward to their expanded offerings and prepared meals. Apparently they will have a fresh juice bar and will also have cold brew coffee soon so their offerings will be quite comprehensive. They have a great indoor/outdoor patio that is covered and should work as a four season dining area. Thankfully it is non-smoking and has a couple outdoor fans. The Common Market "Oakwold" is a cool spot for a quick bite or a hangout where you can order beer on tap or grab your favorite craft beer or wine from the shelves and pop the cap and serve yourself. Glad Common Market chose Oakhurst for their newest location!! We are already regulars and love having them as neighbors.
